name: glycine oxidase
classes: Acting on the CH-NH2 group of donors;
reaction: glycine + H2O + O2 = glyoxylate + NH3 + H2O2 (overall reaction) [RN:R00366]; (1a) glycine + O2 = 2-iminoacetate + H2O2 [RN:R07463]; (1b) 2-iminoacetate + H2O = glyoxylate + NH3 [RN:R10245]
comment: A flavoenzyme containing non-covalently bound FAD. The enzyme from Bacillus subtilis is active with glycine, sarcosine, N-ethylglycine, D-alanine, D-alpha-aminobutyrate, D-proline, D-pipecolate and N-methyl-D-alanine. It differs from EC 1.4.3.3, D-amino-acid oxidase, due to its activity on sarcosine and D-pipecolate. The intermediate 2-iminoacetate is used directly by EC 2.8.1.10, thiazole synthase.

references.title: Glycine oxidase from Bacillus subtilis. Characterization of a new flavoprotein.
Purification and characterization of a novel glycine oxidase from Bacillus subtilis.
